## The Architecture Diagram

Here is a simplified view of how these components connect:
```
                        Internet
                            │
                            │ HTTPS only
                            ▼
                 ┌─────────────────────┐
                 │    AWS Cloud (VPC)   │
                 │                     │
                 │  ┌───────────────┐  │
                 │  │  EC2 Instance │  │
                 │  │  (OpenMRS     │  │
                 │  │  Application) │  │
                 │  └──────┬────────┘  │
                 │         │           │
                 │  Private subnet     │
                 │         │           │
                 │  ┌──────▼────────┐  │
                 │  │  RDS Database │  │
                 │  │  (Patient     │  │
                 │  │  Records)     │  │
                 │  └──────┬────────┘  │
                 │         │           │
                 │  ┌──────▼────────┐  │
                 │  │  S3 Bucket    │  │
                 │  │  (Backups)    │  │
                 │  └───────────────┘  │
                 │                     │
                 │  Security Groups    │
                 │  control all        │
                 │  traffic flows      │
                 └─────────────────────┘
```

Working through this diagram made the architecture concrete in a way that reading about it alone did not. Each arrow represents a data flow — and each data flow is a potential attack surface if not properly controlled.

