## What I Am Still Thinking About

One thing I want to explore further is how the architecture changes as OpenMRS scales. The deployment I described today is appropriate for a small to medium healthcare organization. But OpenMRS is also used in large-scale national health system implementations — in some countries it supports millions of patient records across hundreds of facilities.

At that scale, the architecture becomes significantly more complex — load balancers, multi-region deployments, database replication, more sophisticated identity management. Do the GRC principles stay the same? I believe the answer is yes — the fundamentals of risk assessment, shared responsibility, and compliance do not change with scale. But the complexity of applying them increases significantly, and I am curious about what that looks like in practice.

